Error: Error: "Can'T Connect To The Server" Message Is Displayed When Trying To Join A Minecraft Server.

Solution: 1. Check your internet connection to make sure it is stable and functioning properly.
2. Make sure that the server is online and not under maintenance.
3. Verify that the username and the IP address entered are correct.
4. Make sure that you have a legal and purchased version of Minecraft.
5. Check if there are any network issues or firewall settings that might be blocking your connection
